08/11/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias inaugurated on Saturday (November 7th) a new airport in Larnaca.
The ceremony was also attended by local and foreign officials including France's European Affairs Minister Pierre Lellouche.
"Today serves as a landmark for the tourism development and the island's infrastructure," Christofias said, adding that the airport will play a significant role in efforts to make Cyprus a major transit hub.
The airport was built by a consortium of French and local companies and cost some 656m euros.
It is expected to be able to serve some 7.5m passengers a year.
(DPA, AFP - 07/11/09)
